<div id="review_2361994411" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2361994411" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1394928-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1405367803p2/1394928.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2361994411?book_show_action=true">Apr 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/1394928-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=nf">nf</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=lib-has-audio">lib-has-audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=library">library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=library-request">library-request</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=business">business</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1394928-laura?shelf=memoirs">memoirs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2361994411" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer118027918938980293">Five wonderful stars. I knew after watching Comey&apos;s congressional testimony that if he ever wrote a book, I would be interested in reading it. However, I was unprepared for what turned out to be an inspirational page turner. <br/><br/>I was lucky enough to obtain the book and cd book from the library on Saturday because I had got on the hold list for this some time ago. I wasn&apos;t sure the timing for this would be right, so I thought I would do a quick flick-through and in all likelihood table it for a more</span>
  <span id="freeText118027918938980293" style="display:none">Five wonderful stars. I knew after watching Comey's congressional testimony that if he ever wrote a book, I would be interested in reading it. However, I was unprepared for what turned out to be an inspirational page turner. <br /><br />I was lucky enough to obtain the book and cd book from the library on Saturday because I had got on the hold list for this some time ago. I wasn't sure the timing for this would be right, so I thought I would do a quick flick-through and in all likelihood table it for a more settled time. It sucked me right in, though. This guy is a writer! I didn't expect he would be able to hook me from page one. <br /><br />Comey has had some personal and professional life experiences that made this book quite compelling. He was a victim of violent crime as a teen, almost died as a young adult, lost an infant child as a young father of three, and served as both the Deputy Attorney General in a Republican administration and Director of the FBI in a Democratic administration. He's also worked at big law firms and large corporate organizations. So if the only thing you are looking for is a book about ethical leadership written by someone with a pretty interesting life, this is a great choice. But this book is much more than that. <br /><br />Despite what partisans on both sides of the political aisle may think or believe about Comey, all he really is is someone who cares about doing a difficult job right. He is a husband and father first, and everything else second. He is passionate about the truth. He has opinions, but he's a straight-shooter. And that's what I was looking for in this account. I just wanted someone who was there, who knows a lot more about the current climate than I do, to lay out the facts and allow me to draw my own conclusions. <br /><br />After several hours reading this book, I went to bed listening to the audio version, read by the author. Once again, this author surprised me in that he narrated this book really well. Authors aren't usually good at this. I was awake from 10pm until midnight, riveted. I finally had to switch audiobooks so I would be able to fall asleep. That doesn't usually happen to me, even with really good fiction. It even brought me to tears several times. Again, quite unexpected. <br /><br />So yes, this was five stars for me, all the way through. Not at all what I expected, but much better. I hope he continues to write, because he really has a gift for it. This is a highly readable account of ethical leadership, using examples from the author's own background. I enjoyed every page of this, and highly recommend it. At least half of it has nothing to do with politics. So you definitely do not have to be a political hound to enjoy it. I found it a fair and balanced account. I'd love to read about ten more just like this. <br /><br />Book and audiobook, five stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="118027918938980293" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


